# https://alloc.cyber.com.au/task/task.php?taskID=31276
Package: prisonpc-core-fonts
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
# UI font family — DejaVu
 fonts-dejavu-core,
 fonts-dejavu-extra,
# Print font family — Liberation 2
# Replaces Adobe family (Helvetica/Times/Courier)
# Replaces MS XP family (Arial/TimesNewRoman/CourierNew)
# Replaces GNU Freefont family
# Replaces Liberation 1 family
# Replaces CrOS Core family
 fonts-liberation2,
# Print font family extras
# Replaces MS Vista family (Cambria/Calibri/Consolas)
# https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Windows_Vista_typefaces
 fonts-crosextra-carlito,
 fonts-crosextra-caladea,
 fonts-inconsolata,
# Fallback font family — Noto
# Replaces Droid Sans Fallback
# NOTE: fonts-noto-cjk not installed ∵ huge install footprint.
# NOTE: fonts-noto-unhinted not installed ∵ no demand.
 fonts-noto-hinted,
 fonts-noto-mono
Provides:  fonts-linuxlibertine, fonts-freefont-ttf, fonts-liberation, fonts-croscore, fonts-droid-fallback
Conflicts: fonts-linuxlibertine, fonts-freefont-ttf, fonts-liberation, fonts-croscore, fonts-droid-fallback
Replaces:  fonts-linuxlibertine, fonts-freefont-ttf, fonts-liberation, fonts-croscore, fonts-droid-fallback
Architecture: all
Description: core PrisonPC fonts
 This package ensures the best implementation of core fonts are installed.
 .
 Tinos (CrOS Core) covers about 2.5k codepoints.
 FreeSerif (GNU FreeFont) covers about 10.5k codepoints.
 Droid Sans Fallback covers about 50k codepoints.
 This package also prevents other implementations of core fonts from being
 installed, and provides compatibility symlinks for same.
 .
 We install Droid Sans Fallback,
 so there is no need to provide FreeFont to provide a "fallback font".
 This is necessary because legacy apps like upmc, minetest, childsplay and
 gargoyle-free do not use fontconfig to find the system default font, but
 instead hard-code the path to a specific font file.
 .
 Our recommended usage is:
 .
  * DejaVu Sans / Serif / Sans Mono for screen UI elements.
  * CrOS Core Tinos / Arimo / Cousine for printing & office docs.
  * Droid Sans Fallback for any codepoints note covered above.
 .
 NOTE: As at Jul 2016, Droid Sans Fallback is called "Noto Sans Mono".
 The references to Droid above are because Jessie predates this change.
